Description: My 2 year old has a small fever and is vomiting. I'm worried about her. Are these symptoms of the Coronavirus?
DialogueText:
Patient:
My 2 year old has a small fever and is vomiting. I'm worried about her. Are these symptoms of the Coronavirus?
Doctor:
Probably not. much more important is what her exposure is to anyone who has COVID19 or traveler from a highly infected area.fever >100.4F and respiratory symptoms are more common with COVID 19 than vomiting.
